      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>creamed coconut</strong> and the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>tamari soy sauce</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your<strong> coconut stock</strong></p><p>Wash the <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once the green beans are starting to brown, add the <strong>spinach </strong>and the<strong> coconut stock </strong>to the pan and cook for 1-2 min further or until the spinach has wilted and the sauce has slightly reduced – this is your <strong>coconut veg</strong></p>",
